@startuml object-watermark
'' ============================================================================
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this is an OBJECT/COMPONENT pipeline showing
'' how a single monochrome SVG asset is re-tinted by a CSS mask into a themed
'' emblem. Mermaid has no first-class object diagram with typed compartments and
'' per-object fill colors; PlantUML's `rectangle`+`card` with inline per-element
'' colors lets each transformation stage carry the palette color of the concept
'' it belongs to (filesystem asset, IPC-less renderer CSS, app token).
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Watermark emblem pipeline — shield.svg → CSS mask → themed silhouette

'' ---- the source asset (filesystem / static resource = tan) ----
rectangle "shield.svg\n(resources/public/assets)" as SVG FS_COLOR {
  card "viewBox 0 0 240 290\nstroke = currentColor\nfill   = currentColor\nheraldic shield + tree-of-life\n+ 'VINARY TREE' wordmark" as SVGBODY #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- the CSS rule that turns the asset into a tintable silhouette (renderer = teal) ----
rectangle ".vv-shield  (app.css)" as SHIELD RENDERER_COLOR {
  card "width  : 300px\nheight : 360px" as BOX #FBF8EF
  card "mask : url(../assets/shield.svg)\n       center / contain no-repeat\n(only opaque SVG pixels survive)" as MASK #FBF8EF
  card "background-color : var(--vv-fg)\nopacity          : 0.07" as FILL #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- the active theme palette token (DataScript-purple = a --vv-* token) ----
rectangle "active theme\n(css/themes/<name>.css :root)" as THEME DATASCRIPT_COLOR {
  card "--vv-fg  (base foreground)\ndark : #b2b2b2\nlight: #655370" as FGVAR #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- the rendered result inside the empty content pane ----
rectangle "rendered emblem\n.vv-watermark > .vv-shield" as OUT #1F6B53 {
  card "a faint, theme-tinted\nVinary Tree silhouette,\ncentered in the empty tab" as EMBLEM #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- wiring (each arrow is one transformation step) ----
SVG  -[#9F8766,thickness=2]->  SHIELD : (1) referenced as a CSS\nmask image (alpha channel)
THEME -[#A45BAD,thickness=2]-> SHIELD : (2) var(--vv-fg) supplies\nthe box fill color
SHIELD -[#2D9574,thickness=2]-> OUT  : (3) box painted in --vv-fg,\nclipped to the shield, @ 7% opacity

note bottom of OUT
  The SVG itself is **never recolored**; the box is filled with the
  theme color and the SVG only **masks** (clips) that fill. Switching
  theme swaps --vv-fg, so the same emblem re-tints with **no asset change**.
end note

legend right
  |= color |= concept |
  | <#9F8766> | filesystem / static SVG asset |
  | <#2D9574> | renderer (Chromium) CSS — no IPC, paint-only |
  | <#A45BAD> | theme palette token (--vv-*) |
  | <#1F6B53> | final rendered emblem |
endlegend
@enduml
